name: pitstop
description: This repo contains a sample application based on a Garage Management System for Pitstop - a fictitious garage. The primary goal of this sample is to demonstrate several software-architecture concepts like: Microservices, CQRS, Event Sourcing, Domain Driven Design (DDD), Eventual Consistency.

description: StockBrokerageSystem is a microservices-based project designed for seamless order management in a stock trading environment. Users can place, modify, and cancel orders, which are recorded in an orderbook.

name: healthcare-appointment-system
description: The Healthcare Appointment System allows patients to schedule, modify, and cancel appointments with healthcare providers. It also supports features like doctor availability management, patient notifications, and medical record integration. The system is built on a microservices architecture, making it scalable, modular, and easy to extend.

name: NIMGuard---Predictive-Maintenance-for-Smart-Factories
description: A real-time predictive maintenance system using NVIDIA Inference Microservices (NIM) and Generative AI models to tackle unexpected equipment failures and inefficient maintenance in smart factories.

name: Stack-OverFlow-2.0
description: This project is a basic implementation of a Stack Overflow-like system built first as a monolithic web-based application and later broken down into microservices. The main goal of this project is to demonstrate the transition from a monolithic architecture to a microservices architecture.

name: sk-notifications
description: ScholaKit is an open source school management system, this is the microservice that manages sending email and text messages. ScholaKit is coded in Java Spring Boot framework and Oracle database.

name: BIS2_satellite-tasking
description: Microservice for a Recommender System that handles satellite tasking, processes tasking recommendations, and retrieves imagery from Landsat, Sentinel, and MODIS via Microsoft Planetary Computer. Developed with Flask for the Business Information Systems 2 course at Politecnico di Milano in collaboration with eGeos and Cherrydata.

name: recommendation-service
description: Scalable microservice-based system for personalized content recommendations. It leverages Docker, Redis, RabbitMQ, and Grafana. LightFM powering the recommendation algorithm. Users receive suggestions based on interaction history, and performance is monitored through detailed metrics visualization.
